strings.heading: Brachiocephalic artery
strings.description: A major blood vessel that branches off the aortic arch and supplies blood to the right side of the head, neck, and upper limb

strings.heading: Left common careoid artery
strings.description: A major blood vessel that originates directly from the aortic arch, supplying blood to the head and neck, and it does not directly connect to the heart itself

strings.heading: Left subclavian artery
strings.description: Responsible for supplies blood to the left upper body, including the head, neck, and arm

strings.heading: Aorta
strings.description: The largest artery in your body, originating from the left ventricle of the heart, and is responsible for carrying oxygen-rich blood to the rest of the body
